Former Mamelodi Sundowns defender Anele Ngcongca has died after he was involved in a car crash on Monday morning. BackpagePix/Deryck Foster * Editor's note: This is a developing story. JOHANNESBURG - Former Mamelodi Sundowns defender Anele Ngcongca has died. Ngcongca was 33. He was involved in a car crash in KwaZulu-Natal on Monday morning. Ngcongca was thrown from the vehicle and died on the scene. His female companion is in a critical condition in hospital. Ngcongca was recently released by Sundowns to play for AmaZulu.